<br>
Your guild will self-destruct in no time with a loot policy like that. Are you trying to be fair? Do you realize that randomness and fairness are NOT the same? I'd say that random rolls are the furthest thing from fair, as it has no intelligence to it.<br>
<br>
In a guild that is obviously totally devoted to obtaining items, you have a loot policy that makes it almost impossible to improve the over-all power of your guild. Your members need gear to become more effective. Your policy basically forces all your members to compete with each-other for needed gear, thereby slowing the entire proccess of equipping your guild.<br>
<br>
I mean, think about it for a second. Why would you sell the MQ of Thurg armor? What droppable items can you really find for the selling price, that are superior to the nodrop thurg armor? There may be some, but I promise you it will not be so, once you reach ToV, or higher.<br>
<br>
I do not mean to offend you, sir, but I think you should carefully re-evaluate your loot system. Perhaps a nice raid-point system for buying loot based on attendance could be developed? As it stands, your guild will no doubt develop an &quot;every-man-for-himself&quot; mentality, which will serve to tear apart your members' cooperation and morale.<br>
<br>
Also, if you're going to /random for loot, you have to use a number higher than 100. If all your level 60's randomed 60-100, you're gonna have to deal with tons of re-rolls, and that gets confusing quickly. Not to mention the logistics involved with recording your entire raid-force's rolls EVERY TIME an item drops...<br>
<br>
I suggest you take a look at the loot policies of Fury's Edge, or some other large, raid-oriented guild. You may be better served with that kind of approach.<br>
<br>
I hope this will help you, and good luck with your guild! <p><center>Argond Valiantfist<br>Grandmaster Geezer of Morell-Thule<br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=133460>Magelo Profile</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/ucarlothecurious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Carlo the Curious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blackburrow Trainee</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#628CBC>(9/2/02 4:40:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://mysite.freeserve.com/moscacr/pstgif.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New guild, named Imperium, forming. Not NBG based.</span><hr size=1> Already heavily discussed in this thread:<br>
